&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>Linux stuff</title><link>https://lutzky.net/linux-stuff/</link><pubDate>Sat, 23 Mar 2013 21:52:36 +0000</pubDate><author>lutzky@gmail.com (Ohad Lutzky)</author><guid>https://lutzky.net/linux-stuff/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Here is an assortment of Linux-related tips and tricks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you&amp;rsquo;re tired of hitting your SSH password over and over again, you might
want to take a look at this guide: &lt;a href="https://lutzky.net/linux-stuff/ssh-public-key-authentication" rel=""&gt;SSH Public Key
Authentication&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you&amp;rsquo;re a Technion student taking the Matam course, you should definitely
check out the &lt;a href="http://www.underwar.co.il/document-details.asp?id=293" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreffer "&gt;Matam
Guide&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here is a list of lectures I&amp;rsquo;ve given in &lt;a href="http://haifux.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreffer "&gt;Haifux&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="http://haifux.org/lectures/127" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreffer "&gt;Lightning Talks 2005 (w/Many others)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="http://haifux.org/lectures/129" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreffer "&gt;LIRC - Infrared Remote Control (w/Alon Altman)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="http://haifux.org/lectures/138" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreffer "&gt;WiFi in Linux&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.shlomifish.org/lecture/Vim/beginners/slides/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreffer "&gt;The VIM Editor for
beginners&lt;/a&gt; (Rerun of
Shlomi&amp;rsquo;s lecture)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="http://haifux.org/lectures/147" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreffer "&gt;FatNS - How to develop a DNS forensics tool&lt;/a&gt;
(w/Boaz Goldstein)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="http://haifux.org/lectures/152-sil" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreffer "&gt;Linux for CS Students - a Primer&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="http://haifux.org/lectures/153-sil1" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreffer "&gt;Linux for CS Students - Debugging&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you&amp;rsquo;re with a russian keyboard and need a stress sign, try &lt;a href="https://lutzky.net/russian-stress" rel=""&gt;/russian-stress&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>SSH public key authentication</title><link>https://lutzky.net/linux-stuff/ssh-public-key-authentication/</link><pubDate>Sat, 23 Mar 2013 21:51:06 +0000</pubDate><author>lutzky@gmail.com (Ohad Lutzky)</author><guid>https://lutzky.net/linux-stuff/ssh-public-key-authentication/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;If you find yourself logging into SSH servers a lot, you might find this tip
useful - you&amp;rsquo;ll only need to type your password once per session. But first,
let&amp;rsquo;s set the default username (so you don&amp;rsquo;t have to tell SSH what user you are
every time):&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;div class="chroma"&gt;
&lt;table class="lntable"&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class="lntd"&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt;2
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt;3
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt;4
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt;5
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt;6
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt;7
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt;8
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class="lntd"&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-console" data-lang="console"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="gp"&gt;$&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nb"&gt;cd&lt;/span&gt; ~
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="gp"&gt;$&lt;/span&gt; mkdir .ssh
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="gp"&gt;$&lt;/span&gt; chmod &lt;span class="m"&gt;700&lt;/span&gt; .ssh
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="gp"&gt;$&lt;/span&gt; cat &amp;gt;&amp;gt; .ssh/config
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="go"&gt;Host t2.technion.ac.il
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="go"&gt;	User slutzky
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="go"&gt;Ctrl-D
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="go"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="gp"&gt;$&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Now, create a public/private key pair for SSH, like so:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Russian stress mark</title><link>https://lutzky.net/russian-stress/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>lutzky@gmail.com (Ohad Lutzky)</author><guid>https://lutzky.net/russian-stress/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;This is a handy little page for copying the stress mark (acute mark) to clipboard. Useful if your Russian
